17/07/2006
KUMANOVO, Macedonia -- A new incident involving the ethnic Albanian bloc in Macedonia was reported in the town of Kumanovo early Sunday (16 July), when unknown perpetrators attacked the election headquarters of the Democratic Party of Albanians (DPA). Kumanovo police are investigating. DPA municipal branch chief Granit Osmani described it as the second attack on DPA's office in Kumanovo in the past two months and again blamed a rival party, the Democratic Union of Integration. (Vecer - 17/07/06; Makfax, A1 TV - 16/07/06)
